===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|bakhous|lang=enm}}, {{term|bachous|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|bæchus|bæchūs|bakery, bakehouse|lang=ang}}, equivalent to {{compound|bake|house}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|bake-hous||bakehouse, bakery|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|backhus||bakehouse|lang=nds}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A building or an apartment used for the preparing and baking of bread and other baked goods.
# A building principally containing [[ovens]].

